               <msContents>
                  <summary>Images 2r-4l: Angels Praise Her, Yǝwedǝssǝwa Mäla’ǝkt, ይዌድስዋ፡ መላእክት፡ ለማርያም፡. Répertoire 388; MD 519ff. ; EMML 1593, <locus target="#92a">fol. 92a</locus>. Images 5r-163l: Psalter.  The Psalms open with the prayer from the Psalter of the Virgin. The midpoint of the psalms is unmarked. Many of the occurrences of the word for God are written in alternating red and black ink. Psalm 151 is the short version. The superscription to the fourth biblical canticle is the common one. Song of Songs is the common version. The Praises of Mary begin on Monday and culminate on Sunday. The harags are of the type produced in the Menilek and Selassie scriptoria. The illuminations appear to be added recently.</summary>
